[birds chirping]

25
00:01:00,125 --> 00:01:03,083
[pleasant piano music]

26
00:01:03,166 --> 00:01:06,666
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:09,166
[male narrator] <i>George loved</i>
<i>playing hide n' seek…</i>

28
00:01:11,375 --> 00:01:14,375
<i>And playing with Charkie was</i>
<i>a special challenge.</i>

29
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:19,500
<i>George couldn't outsmart</i>
<i>Charkie's super sense of smell!</i>

30
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:21,666
[grunting in defeat]

31
00:01:21,750 --> 00:01:25,125
[chatters excitedly]

32
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:26,458
[barking]

33
00:01:27,875 --> 00:01:30,833
[chattering happily]

34
00:01:32,250 --> 00:01:35,250
[grunting, counting]

35
00:01:39,791 --> 00:01:42,291
[whimpering]

36
00:01:42,375 --> 00:01:44,208
[grunting, counting]

37
00:01:44,291 --> 00:01:46,291
[thunder rumbling]

38
00:01:46,375 --> 00:01:48,541
[grunting excitedly]

39
00:01:48,625 --> 00:01:50,791
[chattering curiously]

40
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:59,708
-[grunting excitedly]
-[thunder rumbles]

41
00:01:59,791 --> 00:02:02,625
[narrator] <i>George loved watching</i>
<i>a good storm,</i>

42
00:02:02,708 --> 00:02:05,333
<i>but first, he needed to</i>
<i>find Charkie.</i>

43
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:09,875
-[whimpering]
-[chatters]

44
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:12,375
[narrator] <i>That wasn't a very</i>
<i>good place to hide.</i>

45
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:14,500
[chattering triumphantly]

46
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:17,458
[whimpering]

47
00:02:17,541 --> 00:02:19,208
Time for lunch.

48
00:02:20,250 --> 00:02:23,458
It's my famous Pesto Pasta
with Parsley &amp; Peas.

49
00:02:23,541 --> 00:02:24,708
[chatters excitedly]

50
00:02:24,791 --> 00:02:27,416
And for our guest,
my famous

51
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:29,291
uh…kibble.

52
00:02:29,375 --> 00:02:31,375
[panting, barking]

53
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:33,166
[panting]

54
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:35,708
[thunder booming]

55
00:02:35,791 --> 00:02:37,500
[barks in fright]

56
00:02:37,583 --> 00:02:39,916
-Whoa!
-[yelping]

57
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,416
[sighs]

58
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:44,291
Maybe instead we'll have
my famous…

59
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:45,666
something else.

60
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,666
[narrator]
<i>Where was Charkie going?</i>

61
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:51,208
<i>It was George's turn to hide.</i>

62
00:02:51,291 --> 00:02:52,875
-[whimpering]
-[chatters curiously]

63
00:02:52,958 --> 00:02:55,416
[narrator] <i>This was also not</i>
<i>a very good place to hide.</i>

64
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,750
[chatters excitedly]

65
00:02:57,833 --> 00:02:59,583
-[whimpering]
-[grunts curiously]

66
00:02:59,666 --> 00:03:01,291
[whimpering]

67
00:03:02,208 --> 00:03:04,458
[narrator] <i>Why was Charkie</i>
<i>so afraid all of a sudden?</i>

68
00:03:04,541 --> 00:03:06,375
[piano chords]

69
00:03:08,375 --> 00:03:10,541
[howls]

70
00:03:10,625 --> 00:03:14,208
Huh, it's a miracle I didn't
get any on my shirt.

71
00:03:14,291 --> 00:03:16,791
-[barking]
-Ooh!

72
00:03:16,875 --> 00:03:18,916
Spoke too soon.

73
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:21,875
-[thunder rumbling]
-[howling]

74
00:03:21,958 --> 00:03:23,916
[whimpering]

75
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,875
[chatters inquisitively]

76
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:29,583
Hm.

77
00:03:29,666 --> 00:03:31,375
She must be afraid of storms.

78
00:03:31,458 --> 00:03:33,208
Lots of dogs are.

79
00:03:33,833 --> 00:03:36,416
Aw.
Poor Charkie.

80
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,958
We're here with you.

81
00:03:39,041 --> 00:03:41,666
[chatters encouragingly]

82
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:45,416
[narrator] <i>George wondered why</i>
<i>Charkie was scared of storms.</i>

83
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:49,458
[chatters contemplatively]

84
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:51,375
[narrator] <i>He thought they were</i>
<i>kind of exciting.</i>

85
00:03:51,458 --> 00:03:53,250
[thunder rumbles]

86
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,375
[chatters happily]

87
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:57,958
[narrator]<i> Maybe Charkie just</i>
<i>didn't like all that rain?</i>

88
00:03:58,041 --> 00:04:00,958
[barking excitedly]

89
00:04:01,041 --> 00:04:03,583
[water splatters]

90
00:04:05,916 --> 00:04:07,375
[narrator] <i>No</i>.

91
00:04:07,458 --> 00:04:09,875
<i>Charkie loved any excuse</i>
<i>to get wet.</i>

92
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:12,000
<i>It had to be something else.</i>

93
00:04:12,083 --> 00:04:13,333
[thunder rumbles]

94
00:04:13,416 --> 00:04:14,583
[chatters curiously]

95
00:04:14,666 --> 00:04:16,500
[narrator]
<i>Could it be the loud noise</i>

96
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:18,750
<i>the thunder made?</i>

97
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:20,666
<i>There was only one way</i>
<i>to find out…</i>

98
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:23,750
[grunting excitedly]

99
00:04:25,625 --> 00:04:28,333
A little dish soap
should get this out…

100
00:04:28,416 --> 00:04:30,000
[banging loudly]
[gasps]

101
00:04:30,083 --> 00:04:31,333
Oh!

102
00:04:31,416 --> 00:04:33,666
[banging continues]

103
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:35,750
-[chatters curiously]
-[barks]

104
00:04:35,833 --> 00:04:37,958
[giggles]

105
00:04:39,625 --> 00:04:40,791
[narrator]<i> Nope.</i>

106
00:04:40,875 --> 00:04:43,750
<i>It wasn't the loud noise,</i>
<i>either.</i>

107
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,375
[chatters curiously]

108
00:04:45,458 --> 00:04:47,708
[narrator] <i>What else</i>
<i>happened during a storm?</i>

109
00:04:47,791 --> 00:04:49,375
[piano chords]

110
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,666
[chatters triumphantly]

111
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:55,041
[narrator] <i>Lightning!</i>

112
00:04:55,125 --> 00:04:57,000
-[thunder rumbles]
-[howling]

113
00:04:57,083 --> 00:04:59,375
[barking]

114
00:05:00,875 --> 00:05:04,291
[barking happily]

115
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:07,875
[toy squeaks]

116
00:05:10,500 --> 00:05:11,875
[narrator] <i>Nope.</i>

117
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:15,083
<i>Charkie wasn't afraid</i>
<i>of flashes of light.</i>

118
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:20,375
[howls]

119
00:05:20,458 --> 00:05:22,458
-[thunder booms]
-[narrator] <i>Except that kind.</i>

120
00:05:22,541 --> 00:05:25,750
Okay.
More kibble for Charkie.

121
00:05:25,833 --> 00:05:28,000
And peanut butter and banana
sandwiches for us!

122
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:30,750
-[barking]
-Ow!

123
00:05:30,833 --> 00:05:32,791
[grunts]

124
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:34,791
Oh.

125
00:05:34,875 --> 00:05:37,041
[chatters happily]

126
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:39,916
[grunting excitedly]

127
00:05:41,458 --> 00:05:42,708
[whining]

128
00:05:42,791 --> 00:05:44,958
[thunder rumbles]

129
00:05:45,041 --> 00:05:47,750
Seems like the storm
is getting closer.

130
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,875
-[chatters curiously]
-Yeah.

131
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:52,083
You can tell how close
or far a storm is

132
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:54,875
by counting the seconds between
the lightning and thunder.

133
00:05:54,958 --> 00:05:56,583
[chatters inquisitively]

134
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,083
Quick, start counting.

135
00:06:00,166 --> 00:06:03,041
One, two, three,

136
00:06:03,125 --> 00:06:05,041
four, five--

137
00:06:05,125 --> 00:06:06,833
[thunder rumbles]

138
00:06:06,916 --> 00:06:09,125
The last time I counted,
it was six seconds,

139
00:06:09,208 --> 00:06:10,750
so it's getting closer.

140
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:13,666
But don't worry.
We're safe in here.

141
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:15,125
[electricity crackles]
[all gasp]

142
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,833
It's okay.
It's okay.

143
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,750
The storm just knocked
out the power.

144
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:20,666
I'll get some flashlights.

145
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:23,083
[barks, whines]

146
00:06:23,166 --> 00:06:24,541
[chatters]

147
00:06:26,708 --> 00:06:28,375
-[whimpers]
-Well.

148
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:29,916
I'll get there eventually.

149
00:06:30,875 --> 00:06:32,916
[grunts triumphantly]

150
00:06:34,416 --> 00:06:35,708
Aw. Hm.

151
00:06:35,791 --> 00:06:36,958
[clicking]

152
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:38,583
Huh?

153
00:06:38,666 --> 00:06:39,875
[chatters in confusion]

154
00:06:39,958 --> 00:06:41,500
[clicking]

155
00:06:41,583 --> 00:06:43,041
Huh.

156
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:45,750
George, did you use up
the batteries

157
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,541
playing with
the flashlights again?

158
00:06:47,625 --> 00:06:50,666
[jaunty music]

159
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:55,000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

160
00:06:55,083 --> 00:06:58,666
[chatters sheepishly]

161
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:02,000
[sighs] I'll go ask
the Doorman for some batteries.

162
00:07:02,083 --> 00:07:05,541
[whining]

163
00:07:08,083 --> 00:07:11,083
[grunting excitedly]

164
00:07:11,166 --> 00:07:12,500
Good idea.

165
00:07:12,583 --> 00:07:13,666
Oh, it's his lunch hour,

166
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,083
so he might be
in his apartment.

167
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:16,708
[chatters]

168
00:07:17,875 --> 00:07:19,500
[grunts excitedly]

169
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:22,083
[whines]

170
00:07:24,291 --> 00:07:25,875
[gasps]

171
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:27,708
[grunting, counting "1, 2"]

172
00:07:27,791 --> 00:07:29,583
[thunder rumbles]

173
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:31,000
[narrator]
<i>There were only 2 seconds</i>

174
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:32,958
<i>between the lightning</i>
<i>and thunder.</i>

175
00:07:33,041 --> 00:07:34,958
<i>The storm was getting closer!</i>

176
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:40,166
[chattering happily]

177
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:41,625
[door creaks]

178
00:07:42,541 --> 00:07:43,916
[door creaking]

179
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,500
[chattering loudly]
[music playing softly]

180
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:49,541
[narrator] <i>The Doorman's</i>
<i>apartment seemed to be empty.</i>

181
00:07:49,625 --> 00:07:52,041
<i>But where was that music</i>
<i>coming from?</i>

182
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:55,041
[soft music playing]

183
00:07:55,125 --> 00:07:56,166
<i>♪ ♪</i>

184
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:57,791
[grunting softly]

185
00:07:58,791 --> 00:08:01,166
[narrator] <i>Hundley wasn't scared</i>
<i>of this storm at all.</i>

186
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03,666
[thunder rumbles]

187
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:06,666
[yawns]

188
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:10,916
[narrator] <i>In fact, he didn't</i>
<i>even notice it!</i>

189
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,250
<i>Maybe Hundley could tell George</i>
<i>how to keep Charkie</i>

190
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:14,958
<i>calm during the storm.</i>

191
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,041
[chattering inquisitively]

192
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:23,041
[barking]

193
00:08:24,583 --> 00:08:25,833
[thunder booms]

194
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:26,916
[whines]

195
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:29,250
[whimpering]

196
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:32,582
[chatters curiously]

197
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:35,750
[narrator] <i>So Hundley  was</i>
<i>afraid of the storm.</i>

198
00:08:35,832 --> 00:08:37,207
Oh, hi, George.

199
00:08:37,291 --> 00:08:39,082
Is the Doorman home?

200
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:40,666
[chatters happily]

201
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:42,875
[grunts negatively]

202
00:08:42,957 --> 00:08:45,666
Oh, then he must be
in the lobby.

203
00:08:45,750 --> 00:08:47,750
I need batteries
for my flashlight.

204
00:08:47,833 --> 00:08:50,208
[chatters affirmatively]

205
00:08:53,041 --> 00:08:55,125
Batteries?
Sure!

206
00:08:55,208 --> 00:08:57,125
Help yourself.

207
00:08:57,208 --> 00:08:59,791
[thunder booming]

208
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:03,041
Thanks again for the tip
about the safe space.

209
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:06,875
My dog has never been so calm
during a storm.

210
00:09:07,708 --> 00:09:10,750
[chattering questioningly]

211
00:09:10,833 --> 00:09:14,750
A safe space is a place dogs
can go during a storm.

212
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,541
[grunts excitedly]

213
00:09:16,625 --> 00:09:19,125
They relax there
because they can't hear

214
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:21,000
or see the storm.

215
00:09:21,083 --> 00:09:24,750
[chatters comprehensively]

216
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:27,083
[narrator] <i>That's why Hundley</i>
<i>could sleep through the storm!</i>

217
00:09:27,166 --> 00:09:29,625
<i>The music distracted him</i>
<i>from the thunder.</i>

218
00:09:29,708 --> 00:09:32,000
<i>And he couldn't see</i>
<i>the lightning from the closet.</i>

219
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:35,166
<i>It was exactly</i>
<i>what Charkie needed!</i>

220
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,833
[chatters in question]

221
00:09:37,916 --> 00:09:39,791
Take as many as you like.

222
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:41,583
I've got tons of 'em.

223
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:44,125
[chatters appreciatively]

224
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:47,333
[grunting excitedly]

225
00:09:47,416 --> 00:09:50,000
-[panting, whining]
-[strains]

226
00:09:50,083 --> 00:09:52,000
Ooh. Hey, Charkie.
[thunder rumbles]

227
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:53,583
[whines]

228
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:56,291
How about I just stretch
my legs a little?

229
00:09:56,375 --> 00:09:57,833
[sighs]

230
00:09:57,916 --> 00:10:00,125
[grunting excitedly]

231
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:02,208
[chatters triumphantly]

232
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:05,708
Boy, am I glad to see you,
George.

233
00:10:05,791 --> 00:10:07,916
-[grunting]
-Wait, I--

234
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,291
[sighs]

235
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:11,000
[chattering happily]

236
00:10:14,125 --> 00:10:16,833
[narrator] <i>A safe space needed</i>
<i>a comfy bed…</i>

237
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,958
Um. George?

238
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,625
[narrator] <i>Nice lighting…</i>

239
00:10:24,708 --> 00:10:25,833
[grunts]

240
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:28,750
[narrator] <i>Soothing music…</i>

241
00:10:28,833 --> 00:10:30,625
[radio static,
soft music plays]

242
00:10:31,291 --> 00:10:33,000
And snacks!

243
00:10:35,958 --> 00:10:39,708
Now all Charkie's safe space
needed was Charkie!

244
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:41,208
[toy squeaking]

245
00:10:41,291 --> 00:10:43,875
[chattering encouragingly]

246
00:10:43,958 --> 00:10:45,708
[barking]

247
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:51,208
[chattering happily]

248
00:10:52,166 --> 00:10:53,416
[sighs]

249
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:54,875
[bones crack]
Oh.

250
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:58,083
[chatters happily]

251
00:10:58,166 --> 00:11:00,958
[barking]

252
00:11:01,041 --> 00:11:03,875
[narrator] <i>Finally!</i>
<i>Charkie was calm.</i>

253
00:11:03,958 --> 00:11:05,166
[barking happily]

254
00:11:06,041 --> 00:11:07,875
[toy squeaking]

255
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:09,250
[gasps]

256
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:13,000
[grunting, counting
"1, 2, 3, 4"]

257
00:11:13,083 --> 00:11:15,791
[thunder rumbling]

258
00:11:16,458 --> 00:11:18,291
[narrator] <i>The time between</i>
<i>the lightning and thunder</i>

259
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:20,333
<i>was getting longer again!</i>

260
00:11:20,416 --> 00:11:23,000
<i>That meant the storm</i>
<i>was moving away.</i>

261
00:11:24,375 --> 00:11:26,416
<i>And Charkie was happy.</i>

262
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:29,125
<i>The safe space had worked.</i>

263
00:11:29,208 --> 00:11:31,458
What's going on in here?

264
00:11:31,541 --> 00:11:34,833
[chatters excitedly]

265
00:11:34,916 --> 00:11:37,958
Wow. This is pretty cozy.

266
00:11:45,791 --> 00:11:47,416
[piano chords]

267
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,708
[man in the yellow hat]
One, two,

268
00:11:49,791 --> 00:11:52,833
three, four, five,

269
00:11:52,916 --> 00:11:55,166
six--
[thunder booms]

270
00:11:59,416 --> 00:12:02,333
[upbeat piano music]

271
00:12:02,416 --> 00:12:05,791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

272
00:12:05,875 --> 00:12:07,750
[narrator] <i>It was spring</i>
<i>in the city…</i>

273
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:11,541
<i>And things were hopping</i>
<i>at Patty's Posh Pet Parlor.</i>

274
00:12:11,625 --> 00:12:13,916
<i>Including Charkie!</i>

275
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,875
-[barks]
-[grunts happily]

276
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:18,375
[barks]

277
00:12:18,458 --> 00:12:21,333
Sorry.
I'm just getting to Charkie.

278
00:12:21,416 --> 00:12:24,125
With the Dogs of N Avenue
calendar photo shoot today,

279
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:25,291
it's been a busy one!

280
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:27,791
[dogs barking]

281
00:12:27,875 --> 00:12:29,875
[chuckles]
I guess everyone wants to be

282
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,875
in the new
Dogs of N Avenue Calendar!

283
00:12:32,958 --> 00:12:34,041
Yes!

284
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:38,000
Sorry, Steve.
The calendar is just for dogs.

285
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:40,875
[chatters curiously]

286
00:12:40,958 --> 00:12:42,291
The money
from the calendar sales

287
00:12:42,375 --> 00:12:44,458
goes to
our local animal shelter.

288
00:12:44,541 --> 00:12:46,833
-[chatters comprehensively]
-Well,

289
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:49,041
Charkie should be done
in about an hour

290
00:12:49,125 --> 00:12:50,875
if you want to wait for her.

291
00:12:51,458 --> 00:12:54,416
Hm. I have to get
to my xylophone lesson.

292
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:57,583
[defeated sound effect]
Aw!

293
00:12:57,666 --> 00:12:59,583
But Steve isn't doing
anything.

294
00:12:59,666 --> 00:13:02,250
Nothing but saving
the galaxy.

295
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,000
Steve, this is important.

296
00:13:05,083 --> 00:13:06,416
We need you to wait for Charkie

297
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:09,458
and get her to the photoshoot.
Clean.

298
00:13:09,541 --> 00:13:11,416
Sure. Clean.

299
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,416
Uh, photo…

300
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,875
-[defeated sound effect]
-Shoot!

301
00:13:14,958 --> 00:13:16,166
[sighs]

302
00:13:17,166 --> 00:13:20,083
[chatters happily]

303
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:22,916
Great!
Thanks, George!

304
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:24,083
[chatters]

305
00:13:24,166 --> 00:13:26,208
[video game sound effects]

306
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:29,208
Want to help me bathe
Charkie?

307
00:13:29,291 --> 00:13:31,458
[grunts excitedly]

308
00:13:31,541 --> 00:13:34,291
[narrator] <i>George had never</i>
<i>washed a dog before,</i>

309
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:35,916
<i>professionally.</i>

310
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,541
[chatters curiously]

311
00:13:38,625 --> 00:13:41,125
We use this to keep them
in place.

312
00:13:41,208 --> 00:13:43,125
[cheerful music]

313
00:13:43,208 --> 00:13:46,041
[narrator] <i>George was eager</i>
<i>to learn every step.</i>

314
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:49,875
<i>Charkie had to be brushed</i>
<i>to remove tangles.</i>

315
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:57,041
<i>Then she went in a big tub.</i>

316
00:13:57,125 --> 00:13:58,583
[barking]

317
00:14:04,625 --> 00:14:06,541
[narrator] <i>Where she got</i>
<i>rinsed…</i>

318
00:14:08,625 --> 00:14:10,458
<i>Shampooed…</i>

319
00:14:14,041 --> 00:14:15,416
<i>Rinsed again…</i>

320
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:18,916
<i>Then towel dried.</i>

321
00:14:24,041 --> 00:14:27,041
<i>After that came</i>
<i>the detangler…</i>

322
00:14:27,125 --> 00:14:28,458
<i>and combing.</i>

323
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:33,083
<i>And finally there was</i>
<i>a warm fan.</i>

324
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:37,666
[giggles]

325
00:14:39,166 --> 00:14:40,666
And while one dog
is drying,

326
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:43,208
I brush out the dog
I bathed before.

327
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:47,250
[grunting, panting]

328
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,500
-Want to take a ride?
-[chatters in question]

329
00:14:50,541 --> 00:14:51,625
[table whirs]

330
00:14:51,708 --> 00:14:53,250
[grunts excitedly]

331
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:57,166
[chattering happily]

332
00:15:00,125 --> 00:15:01,708
Once the dogs are dry,

333
00:15:01,791 --> 00:15:03,666
they get sprayed
so they smell good.

334
00:15:03,750 --> 00:15:06,166
[sneezes]

335
00:15:11,458 --> 00:15:14,291
And then
they get brushed again.

336
00:15:15,666 --> 00:15:19,166
[narrator]<i> And last of all,</i>
<i>Charkie got a bandana!</i>

337
00:15:20,583 --> 00:15:23,625
Ha-ha!
Here I come, Level 4!

338
00:15:24,791 --> 00:15:27,250
[chatters assertively]

339
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:29,666
Uh, okay.

340
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:32,166
I can take Charkie
from here, George.

341
00:15:33,125 --> 00:15:35,166
[chatters in concern]

342
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:36,500
[barking]

343
00:15:36,583 --> 00:15:38,375
[grunts in dismay]

344
00:15:38,458 --> 00:15:40,500
[barking]

345
00:15:45,125 --> 00:15:47,500
Wow, looks like you had

346
00:15:47,583 --> 00:15:49,750
quite the adventure
since you left.

347
00:15:50,666 --> 00:15:53,041
Uh. Think maybe you could
groom her again

348
00:15:53,125 --> 00:15:54,625
before the photoshoot today?

349
00:15:56,500 --> 00:16:00,333
Well, there are a few dogs
ahead of her.

350
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:03,208
But I can squeeze her in.

351
00:16:06,125 --> 00:16:07,666
[chatters in relief]

352
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:09,500
[beeping]

353
00:16:09,583 --> 00:16:11,250
It's never made
that sound before.

354
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:13,416
No, no, no, that's me.

355
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:15,708
Time to put more money
in the parking meter.

356
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:18,208
Wee. City life!

357
00:16:20,041 --> 00:16:22,125
I'll be back in a few minutes.

358
00:16:23,416 --> 00:16:26,791
Maybe put Charkie in one
of those crates for me, okay?

359
00:16:26,875 --> 00:16:30,375
Now, where did I park my car?

360
00:16:32,375 --> 00:16:33,625
[panting, barks]

361
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:36,541
[chatters happily]

362
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:40,250
[gasps]

363
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:42,625
[narrator] <i>George didn't</i>
<i>know that Hundley got groomed!</i>

364
00:16:42,708 --> 00:16:44,208
[grunts happily]

365
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:46,041
[growling]

366
00:16:46,125 --> 00:16:49,083
Aw, that photoshoot is
in less than two hours.

367
00:16:49,166 --> 00:16:51,750
It took Patty an hour to
groom Charkie the first time.

368
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:54,125
But now she has to groom
all these other dogs

369
00:16:54,208 --> 00:16:56,041
before she can do Charkie.

370
00:16:56,125 --> 00:16:58,708
[narrator] <i>Charkie would</i>
<i>never be done in time.</i>

371
00:17:00,208 --> 00:17:03,125
<i>Unless…somebody helped.</i>

372
00:17:03,208 --> 00:17:04,500
[grunts happily]

373
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:09,250
[chatters]

374
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:11,540
[imitates water spraying]

375
00:17:11,625 --> 00:17:14,540
You think we should
wash the dogs?

376
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:16,290
[chatters affirmatively]

377
00:17:17,290 --> 00:17:19,415
[grunts curiously]

378
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:25,665
[narrator] <i>George had</i>
<i>only helped Patty once,</i>

379
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:28,165
<i>but monkeys</i>
<i>were experts at baths.</i>

380
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:29,375
[chatters worriedly]

381
00:17:29,458 --> 00:17:31,333
[growls]

382
00:17:31,416 --> 00:17:34,500
[narrator] <i>Hundley wasn't</i>
<i>sure what George was up to,</i>

383
00:17:34,583 --> 00:17:37,833
<i>but whatever it was,</i>
<i>he didn't approve.</i>

384
00:17:37,916 --> 00:17:39,333
[grumbling]

385
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:45,416
[chatters encouragingly]

386
00:17:47,458 --> 00:17:49,125
[barks]

387
00:17:49,208 --> 00:17:51,125
[yawns]

388
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:55,875
We'll just have to
put him in.

389
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:01,875
[both grunting]

390
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:06,875
Patty must be super strong
to handle these big dogs!

391
00:18:06,958 --> 00:18:09,375
[narrator] <i>George</i>
<i>was already messing up.</i>

392
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:11,416
[both straining]

393
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:13,750
Hey, we can wash them
from out here.

394
00:18:15,291 --> 00:18:17,166
Aunt Margaret's got one
of these.

395
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:18,708
They stretch.

396
00:18:18,791 --> 00:18:21,666
Patty probably washes
the big dogs on the floor.

397
00:18:23,208 --> 00:18:25,333
[muffled barking]

398
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:27,583
[chatters worriedly]

399
00:18:27,666 --> 00:18:29,416
[narrator] <i>George didn't</i>
<i>remember this happening</i>

400
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,333
<i>with Charkie!</i>

401
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:37,375
<i>Next came the shampoo.</i>

402
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:41,250
<i>Then the rinse.</i>

403
00:18:41,333 --> 00:18:43,375
[barking]

404
00:18:45,333 --> 00:18:48,500
Patty must do nothing
but change clothes all day.

405
00:18:48,583 --> 00:18:51,375
She's always dry
when I see her.

406
00:18:51,458 --> 00:18:52,708
[grunts happily]

407
00:18:53,708 --> 00:18:55,333
[sniffs]

408
00:18:55,416 --> 00:18:57,208
[grunts in disgust]

409
00:18:57,291 --> 00:18:58,916
[narrator]
<i>Goliath was clean now.</i>

410
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,833
<i>But he sure didn't smell</i>
<i>like it.</i>

411
00:19:01,916 --> 00:19:04,333
<i>And then George remembered…</i>

412
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:07,291
<i>He'd forgotten the spray.</i>

413
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,208
[grunts happily]

414
00:19:10,458 --> 00:19:12,416
-[sneezes]
-[sneezes]

415
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:16,666
We're short on time.
We have to hurry!

416
00:19:16,750 --> 00:19:17,875
[chatters]

417
00:19:19,416 --> 00:19:21,208
[grunting excitedly]

418
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:28,291
At least it will be easy
to put this one in the sink.

419
00:19:28,375 --> 00:19:29,666
Ah!

420
00:19:30,958 --> 00:19:34,208
-[grunting]
-[barking]

421
00:19:35,833 --> 00:19:37,666
[chatters triumphantly]

422
00:19:39,708 --> 00:19:42,625
[pleasant piano music]

423
00:19:42,708 --> 00:19:44,875
<i>♪ ♪</i>

424
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:47,416
[narrator] Now what was
he supposed to do?

425
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:50,666
[chatters in thought]

426
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:52,375
[gasps]

427
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:54,333
[chatters happily]

428
00:19:54,416 --> 00:19:56,708
Hey! Good thinking.

429
00:19:57,916 --> 00:19:58,958
[chatters]

430
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,541
[barks, panting]

431
00:20:06,791 --> 00:20:08,958
[chattering happily]

432
00:20:15,458 --> 00:20:16,791
[barks softly]

433
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:29,000
Hey… George, look!

434
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:31,333
I think I broke her fur.

435
00:20:38,041 --> 00:20:39,833
[chatters curiously]

436
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:42,041
[narrator] <i>George</i>
<i>couldn't remember what to do.</i>

437
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:46,500
Yeah. Let's quit
while we're ahe--

438
00:20:46,583 --> 00:20:48,333
Huh?

439
00:20:48,416 --> 00:20:51,416
Oh, this must be how Patty
dries the dogs!

440
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,583
[chatters comprehensively]

441
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:58,458
[narrator]<i> If only George had</i>
<i>a way to remember the steps.</i>

442
00:20:59,458 --> 00:21:00,875
[grunts excitedly]

443
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,375
[narrator]<i> Patty's basket!</i>

444
00:21:03,458 --> 00:21:05,416
<i>That could tell him</i>
<i>about the order!</i>

445
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:07,708
<i>First, was a brush,</i>

446
00:21:07,791 --> 00:21:09,708
<i>second, the shampoo,</i>

447
00:21:09,791 --> 00:21:11,625
<i>third, the towel.</i>

448
00:21:11,708 --> 00:21:13,875
<i>That seemed</i>
<i>like the right order.</i>

449
00:21:14,833 --> 00:21:16,416
[barks in concern]

450
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:18,083
[narrator] <i>There was only one</i>
<i>way to find out!</i>

451
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:19,500
[growls]

452
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:23,833
[narrator]<i> Hundley wondered how</i>
<i>George would make him look bad.</i>

453
00:21:25,791 --> 00:21:27,041
[barks in concern]

454
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,583
[narrator] <i>First the brush.</i>

455
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:33,916
[grunts happily]

456
00:21:37,416 --> 00:21:39,000
[panting happily]

457
00:21:40,666 --> 00:21:43,083
[chattering]

458
00:21:43,166 --> 00:21:45,750
[narrator] <i>Second the shampoo.</i>

459
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,625
[barks happily]

460
00:21:58,875 --> 00:22:00,583
[narrator] <i>Third the towel.</i>

461
00:22:00,666 --> 00:22:01,708
[grunts]

462
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,708
[narrator] <i>Fourth,</i>
<i>the detangler, and the comb.</i>

463
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:16,583
<i>While Hundley was drying,</i>

464
00:22:16,666 --> 00:22:19,000
<i>George and Steve</i>
<i>groomed the other dogs..</i>

465
00:22:19,083 --> 00:22:20,875
<i>Two at a time.</i>

466
00:22:24,708 --> 00:22:26,375
[table whirs]

467
00:22:32,791 --> 00:22:37,041
<i>Once the dogs were dry,</i>
<i>the fifth and sixth steps</i>

468
00:22:37,125 --> 00:22:39,000
<i>were spraying and brushing.</i>

469
00:22:40,833 --> 00:22:42,041
[sneezes]

470
00:22:44,166 --> 00:22:48,041
[narrator] <i>And finally, they</i>
<i>were all groomed to perfection.</i>

471
00:22:48,125 --> 00:22:50,958
<i>In plenty of time</i>
<i>for their close up.</i>

472
00:22:51,041 --> 00:22:52,708
[chatters happily]

473
00:22:52,791 --> 00:22:53,833
[shutter clicks]

474
00:22:55,708 --> 00:22:56,791
I'm back!

475
00:22:58,458 --> 00:22:59,500
Huh.

476
00:23:00,833 --> 00:23:02,750
Where'd everybody go?

477
00:23:04,083 --> 00:23:07,041
[fast swing music]

478
00:23:07,125 --> 00:23:14,125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

